<!--
  Rajlo splash icon — vector drawable converted from
  `public/Rajlo white.svg`. Used by the Android 12+ themed splash
  (`windowSplashScreenAnimatedIcon` in values/styles.xml).

  Why a vector and not the PNG icon foreground that capacitor-assets
  generated?
    1. The PNG was the launcher foreground (the home-screen icon).
       Android extracts that and crops it through a circular mask
       for the splash icon area — wide wordmarks lose most of their
       content to the crop, which is why nothing showed up.
    2. Vectors render at any density without padding/cropping
       surprises and don't need separate mdpi/hdpi/xxxhdpi copies.
    3. Vectors are smaller in the APK than 5 density-specific PNGs.

  Original SVG viewBox is `0 0 343.32 173.36` with every path
  transformed by `translate(-133.9 -316.11)`. We inline that as a
  group translateX/Y so the path data is unchanged from the source
  SVG — make sure to mirror future SVG changes here verbatim.

  Drawable intrinsic size is 288dp square — the Android 12+
  recommendation for splash icons. The wordmark scales to fit
  inside the inner 192dp safe zone with the same aspect ratio as
  the SVG.
-->
